Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech in Charleston, West Virginia, thanking the state for its support in electing President Donald Trump. He praised Trump's commitment to small businesses and his selection of Linda McMahon to lead the Small Business Administration. Pence also discussed the need to repeal and replace Obamacare, highlighting the burden it places on job creators and the American people. He acknowledged that Congress was not able to pass the replacement plan, but expressed confidence that a new plan would be put together in the future. Pence emphasized Trump's focus on creating jobs, cutting taxes, and promoting American energy. He also discussed the administration's commitment to strengthening national security and nominating Judge Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court. Pence encouraged Americans to stand up and be involved in shaping the future of the country.